=== SoH cloud layer (wire v4) end-to-end validation ===
Date:     2026-05-29
Board:    NUCLEO-L476RG + X-NUCLEO-IDB05A2 BLE shield + INA219 @ 0x40
Firmware: nucleo_l476rg_ble_current.conf + CONFIG_BATTERY_SOC_SOH=y (wire v4, MTU 37)
Gateway:  ibattery-gateway run (worktree v4 decoder, from iTerm)
Stack:    InfluxDB 2.9.1 + Grafana 13.0.1

First time State of Health traversed the full pipeline:
firmware -> BLE -> gateway -> InfluxDB -> Grafana.

--- (1) Firmware emits v4 (serial, /dev/cu.usbmodem1203) ---

[v4 t=16047] V=3322 mV T=24.88 C SOC=99.99% PWR=1 CYC=0 flags=0x00000000 I=2.80 mA Q=219.98 mAh
# version tag is "v4" (34-byte packet); SoH carried in the packet, computed on-device.

--- (2) Bug found by THIS E2E (fixed) ---

First gateway run connected + subscribed but NO telemetry arrived. Serial showed:
  Transport send failed: -2        (BATTERY_STATUS_INVALID_ARG)
Root cause: the transport layer has its OWN size constants, separate from the
serializer. BATTERY_TRANSPORT_WIRE_SIZE was still pinned to v3 (32), so ble_send()
rejected the 34-byte v4 packet (len > 32) and the BLE cache buffer was undersized.
The plan/serializer change (battery_serialize.h V4_SIZE=34) had missed it.
Fix: BATTERY_TRANSPORT_WIRE_SIZE_V4=34, BATTERY_TRANSPORT_WIRE_SIZE -> V4, plus a
_Static_assert(BATTERY_TRANSPORT_WIRE_SIZE >= BATTERY_SERIALIZE_V4_SIZE) so it can't
silently regress. (Host unit tests passed throughout — the BLE backend bound is
firmware-only; only the hardware E2E exercised it.)

